What is the use of WebDriverManager.chromedriver().setup();

-> The method WebDriverManager.chromedriver().setup(); is used to automatically download and configure the correct version of ChromeDriver for Selenium WebDriver tests in Java.

üß† Why It‚Äôs Useful:

When you use Selenium with Chrome, you need a compatible version of ChromeDriver that matches the installed version of Google Chrome on your machine. Managing this manually is error-prone and tedious.

WebDriverManager solves this by:

Detecting the version of Chrome installed on your system.

Downloading the matching version of ChromeDriver from the official source.

Setting the system property webdriver.chrome.driver automatically.

Ensuring cross-platform support (Windows, macOS, Linux).

‚úÖ What WebDriverManager.chromedriver().setup(); Does Behind the Scenes:

Checks if Chrome is installed and which version it is.

Checks if a compatible chromedriver binary is already downloaded.

If not, downloads the correct version and caches it locally.

Sets the path to the chromedriver binary in the webdriver.chrome.driver system property, so you don‚Äôt need to set it manually.

üîÅ Before vs After Using WebDriverManager
üî¥ Old Way (Manual):
System.setProperty("webdriver.chrome.driver", "C:\\path\\to\\chromedriver.exe");
WebDriver driver = new ChromeDriver();


You have to manually download and keep updating the driver.

It breaks if Chrome updates.

‚úÖ With WebDriverManager:
WebDriverManager.chromedriver().setup();
WebDriver driver = new ChromeDriver();


Fully automatic.

No need to manage driver files manually.

üì¶ How to Add WebDriverManager to Your Project (Maven):

If you're using Maven, include this in your pom.xml:

<dependency>
    <groupId>io.github.bonigarcia</groupId>
    <artifactId>webdrivermanager</artifactId>
    <version>5.6.3</version> <!-- Check for latest version -->
</dependency>

üß™ Example Code:
import org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver;
import org.openqa.selenium.chrome.ChromeDriver;
import io.github.bonigarcia.wdm.WebDriverManager;

public class Example {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        WebDriverManager.chromedriver().setup();  // Auto setup
        WebDriver driver = new ChromeDriver();
        driver.get("https://www.google.com");
        driver.quit();
    }
}


=============================================================================


import org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver;
import org.openqa.selenium.chrome.ChromeDriver;
import io.github.bonigarcia.wdm.WebDriverManager;

public class Test {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Automatically sets up the ChromeDriver binary
        WebDriverManager.chromedriver().setup();

        WebDriver driver = new ChromeDriver();
        driver.get("https://www.google.com");

        // Do your testing...

        driver.quit();
    }
}

Explanation:
WebDriverManager.chromedriver().setup();
This downloads the appropriate ChromeDriver version and sets the system property for you.

Then, new ChromeDriver(); initializes the driver.

